Example dataset for fixed effects model

Source: R/Data.R
data_FE.Rd

A simulated data set containing response variable, provider information and 4 continuous covariates.

data(data_FE)

Format

A list containing the following elements:

Y

a vector represents the binary outcome

ID

a vector represents the facility indicator (10 facilities in total)

Z

a data frame contains 4 continuous variables

Examples

data(data_FE)
head(data_FE$Y) 
#> [1] 1 0 1 0 0 1
head(data_FE$ID)
#> [1] 3 3 5 3 7 9
head(data_FE$Z)
#>          Z1     Z2      Z3      Z4
#> 129 -1.0518 0.4805  1.1374  1.3395
#> 107 -1.0696 0.0053 -0.4353 -0.5918
#> 237 -0.6108 0.1098 -0.5248  1.4689
#> 131 -0.4967 0.9972  0.5019  0.3900
#> 331  1.5710 2.1165 -0.0759 -0.7802
#> 437 -1.1156 2.2503  0.1843  0.7020
